OL,5,ETWITCHERS ARE OUT FOR THE COUNT        
OL,7,BTheEBritish Trust for Ornithology,Bas  
OL,8,Bpart of the Wetlands Birds survey,     
OL,9,Bplans to have the whole coastEcounted  
OL,10,Bfor waders by the end of January 1998. 
OL,12,BAlthough there is an army of           
OL,13,Bvolunteers, moreEbirdwatchersBare      
OL,14,Bdesperately needed to help out in a few
OL,15,Bareas of Dorset and parts of Cornwall. 
OL,17,BPeople are also needed in areas around 
OL,18,BBangor and Cardigan in Wales, North    
OL,19,BYorkshire and someEScottish islands.   
